x4freetext: .66.2 GRAM IRON OXIDE, ENRICHED TO 97.69 PER CENT
FE-54, IN A 0.03 CM THICK, 8 CM DIAMETER AL CONTAINER
.EACH CAPTURE EVENT WAS WEIGHTED ACCORDING TO ITS
AMPLITUDE INFORMATION IN ORDER TO ACHIEVE A
DETECTOR EFFICIENCY PROPORTIONAL TO THE TOTAL
GAMMA ENERGY RELEASED IN THE CAPTURE PROCESS.
AFTER SUBTRACTING BACKGROUND AND CORRECTING FOR
THE INCIDENT NEUTRON FLUX, THE WEIGHTED COUNT RATES
WERE REDUCED TO RAW CAPTURE CROSS SECTION DATA.
.S-WAVE RESONANCES UP TO 100 KEV WERE ANALYSED
USING A MODIFIED VERSION OF THE R-MATRIX
CONSIDERING THE NEUTRON AND ONE CAPTURE CHANNEL
.NON S-WAVE RESONANCES WERE ANALYSED USING A
SINGLE LEVEL BREIT-WIGNER SHAPE ANALYSIS PROCEDURE
WERE ALSO ANALYSED WITH THE AREA CODE `TACASI`
.NORMALIZATION AT THE 1.15 KEV RESONANCE OF FE-56
.NEUTRON WIDTHS OF KNOWN S-WAVE RESONANCES ( EXCEPT
NON S-WAVE RESONANCES TAKEN FROM M.S.PANDEY+
.THE SHAPE ANALYSIS CODE `FANAC` AND THE AREA
